44#ifndef __ACLINUX_H__
45#define __ACLINUX_H__
46
47#ifdef __KERNEL__
48
49/* ACPICA external files should not include ACPICA headers directly. */
50
51#if !defined(BUILDING_ACPICA) && !defined(_LINUX_ACPI_H)
52#error "Please don't include <acpi/acpi.h> directly, include <linux/acpi.h> instead."
53#endif
54
55#endif
56
57/* Common (in-kernel/user-space) ACPICA configuration */
58
59#define ACPI_USE_SYSTEM_CLIBRARY
60#define ACPI_USE_DO_WHILE_0
61#define ACPI_IGNORE_PACKAGE_RESOLUTION_ERRORS
62
63
64#ifdef __KERNEL__
65
66#define ACPI_USE_SYSTEM_INTTYPES
67#define ACPI_USE_GPE_POLLING
68
69/* Kernel specific ACPICA configuration */
70
71#ifdef CONFIG_ACPI_REDUCED_HARDWARE_ONLY
72#define ACPI_REDUCED_HARDWARE 1
73#endif
74
75#ifdef CONFIG_ACPI_DEBUGGER
76#define ACPI_DEBUGGER
77#endif
78
79#ifdef CONFIG_ACPI_DEBUG
80#define ACPI_MUTEX_DEBUG
81#endif
82
83#include <linux/string.h>
84#include <linux/kernel.h>
85#include <linux/ctype.h>
86#include <linux/sched.h>
87#include <linux/atomic.h>
88#include <linux/math64.h>
89#include <linux/slab.h>
90#include <linux/spinlock_types.h>
91#ifdef EXPORT_ACPI_INTERFACES
92#include <linux/export.h>
93#endif
94#ifdef CONFIG_ACPI
95#include <asm/acenv.h>
96#endif
97
98#define ACPI_INIT_FUNCTION __init
99
100#ifndef CONFIG_ACPI
101
102/* External globals for __KERNEL__, stubs is needed */
103
104#define ACPI_GLOBAL(t,a)
105#define ACPI_INIT_GLOBAL(t,a,b)
106
107/* Generating stubs for configurable ACPICA macros */
108
109#define ACPI_NO_MEM_ALLOCATIONS
110
111/* Generating stubs for configurable ACPICA functions */
112
113#define ACPI_NO_ERROR_MESSAGES
114#undef ACPI_DEBUG_OUTPUT
115
116/* Use a specific bugging default separate from ACPICA */
117
118#undef ACPI_DEBUG_DEFAULT
119#define ACPI_DEBUG_DEFAULT (ACPI_LV_INFO | ACPI_LV_REPAIR)
120
121/* External interface for __KERNEL__, stub is needed */
122
123#define ACPI_EXTERNAL_RETURN_STATUS(Prototype) \
124 static ACPI_INLINE Prototype {return(AE_NOT_CONFIGURED);}
125#define ACPI_EXTERNAL_RETURN_OK(Prototype) \
126 static ACPI_INLINE Prototype {return(AE_OK);}
127#define ACPI_EXTERNAL_RETURN_VOID(Prototype) \
128 static ACPI_INLINE Prototype {return;}
129#define ACPI_EXTERNAL_RETURN_UINT32(Prototype) \
130 static ACPI_INLINE Prototype {return(0);}
131#define ACPI_EXTERNAL_RETURN_PTR(Prototype) \
132 static ACPI_INLINE Prototype {return(NULL);}
133
134#endif /* CONFIG_ACPI */
135
136/* Host-dependent types and defines for in-kernel ACPICA */
137
138#define ACPI_MACHINE_WIDTH BITS_PER_LONG
139#define ACPI_USE_NATIVE_MATH64
140#define ACPI_EXPORT_SYMBOL(symbol) EXPORT_SYMBOL(symbol);
141#define strtoul simple_strtoul
142
143#define ACPI_CACHE_T struct kmem_cache
144#define ACPI_SPINLOCK spinlock_t *
145#define ACPI_CPU_FLAGS unsigned long
146
147/* Use native linux version of AcpiOsAllocateZeroed */
148
149#define USE_NATIVE_ALLOCATE_ZEROED
150
151/*
152 * Overrides for in-kernel ACPICA
153 */
154#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsInitialize
155#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsTerminate
156#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsAllocate
157#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsAllocateZeroed
158#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsFree
159#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsAcquireObject
160#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsGetThreadId
161#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsCreateLock
162
163/*
164 * OSL interfaces used by debugger/disassembler
165 */
166#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsReadable
167#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsWritable
168#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsInitializeDebugger
169#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsTerminateDebugger
170
171/*
172 * OSL interfaces used by utilities
173 */
174#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsRedirectOutput
175#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsGetTableByName
176#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsGetTableByIndex
177#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsGetTableByAddress
178#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsOpenDirectory
179#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsGetNextFilename
180#define ACPI_USE_ALTERNATE_PROTOTYPE_AcpiOsCloseDirectory
181
182#define ACPI_MSG_ERROR KERN_ERR "ACPI Error: "
183#define ACPI_MSG_EXCEPTION KERN_ERR "ACPI Exception: "
184#define ACPI_MSG_WARNING KERN_WARNING "ACPI Warning: "
185#define ACPI_MSG_INFO KERN_INFO "ACPI: "
186
187#define ACPI_MSG_BIOS_ERROR KERN_ERR "ACPI BIOS Error (bug): "
188#define ACPI_MSG_BIOS_WARNING KERN_WARNING "ACPI BIOS Warning (bug): "
189
190/*
191 * Linux wants to use designated initializers for function pointer structs.
192 */
193#define ACPI_STRUCT_INIT(field, value) .field = value
194
195#else /* !__KERNEL__ */
196
197#define ACPI_USE_STANDARD_HEADERS
198
199#ifdef ACPI_USE_STANDARD_HEADERS
200#include <unistd.h>
201#endif
202
203/* Define/disable kernel-specific declarators */
204
205#ifndef __init
206#define __init
207#endif
208#ifndef __iomem
209#define __iomem
210#endif
211
212/* Host-dependent types and defines for user-space ACPICA */
213
214#define ACPI_FLUSH_CPU_CACHE()
215#define ACPI_CAST_PTHREAD_T(Pthread) ((ACPI_THREAD_ID) (Pthread))
216
217#if defined(__ia64__) || (defined(__x86_64__) && !defined(__ILP32__)) ||\
218 defined(__aarch64__) || defined(__PPC64__) ||\
219 defined(__s390x__)
220#define ACPI_MACHINE_WIDTH 64
221#define COMPILER_DEPENDENT_INT64 long
222#define COMPILER_DEPENDENT_UINT64 unsigned long
223#else
224#define ACPI_MACHINE_WIDTH 32
225#define COMPILER_DEPENDENT_INT64 long long
226#define COMPILER_DEPENDENT_UINT64 unsigned long long
227#define ACPI_USE_NATIVE_DIVIDE
228#define ACPI_USE_NATIVE_MATH64
229#endif
230
231#ifndef __cdecl
232#define __cdecl
233#endif
234
235#endif /* __KERNEL__ */
236
237#endif /* __ACLINUX_H__ */
